{
  "text": "The absorption of GnRH by vaginal mucosa is influenced by the state of mucosa (Okada et al. 1984) , mucosal peptidase activity [CITATION_1] , extender composition [CITATION_2] , formulation of analogue [CITATION_3] and, probably, by semen [CITATION_4] ). Additional research is needed to determine the effect of GnRH analogues on rabbit spermatozoa. Because spermatozoa have an important capacity to incorporate foreign molecules (Gandolfi 2000) and could be modified by different proteins and peptides [CITATION_5] ) the harmful effects of GnRH analogues on sperm cannot be excluded.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "35388890",
